text.summary: Examined in this historical context, Googles 20 Percent Time initially appears as nothing more than a variation on time-honored traditions. Though it presents itself as a gift, neo-normative freedom is recallable, contingent, conditional, and deeply subsumed within a contractual logic. But first, I will examine Googles 20 Percent Time policy in relation to the existent literature on worker control. (2006) Official Google blog: Googles 20 percent time in action, The official Google blog [http://googleblog.blogspot.com/2006/05/googles-20-percent-time-in-action.html]. In their Harvard Business Review piece, Davenport and Iyer speak fondly of Googles 20 Percent Time.
